  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "1 Adult Serving = 2 Kids Servings \nHeat the oven to 180°C."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Peel the sweet potatoes and cut into bite-sized chunks. Slice the pepper into thin strips. Tip both into a large baking tray, drizzle with sunflower oil and a pinch of salt, then roast for 25 mins until soft and golden."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, finely grate the garlic and ginger.\nPlace a small saucepan over a medium heat with a splash of sunflower oil. Gently cook the garlic and ginger for 2 mins. Add the peanut butter, soy sauce, honey, curry powder, coconut milk and lime juice. Stir until smooth and gently warmed through, about 3-4 mins, then remove from the heat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cook the rice noodles following pack instructions. Drain, then rinse under cold water to stop them sticking."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Thinly slice the spring onion. Slice the cucumber into half-moons."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Toss the noodles with the satay sauce and a splash of water to loosen it slightly (it will thicken as it cools)."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve up!\nKids Plate: Dish out the noodles and top with the roasted sweet potato and peppers, and cucumber.\nParents Plate: Do the same and add the extra garnish of sliced spring onion."
    }
  ],
  "tips": [
    "To make it vegan, swap the honey for maple syrup.",
    "Works hot or cold — makes a great lunchbox filler.",
    "The sauce thickens quickly — always loosen with water just before serving."
  ],
